[normal]“[The BBC is] currently estimated to have around 7
[normal]0 per cent of all news consumption on both television and radio… The problem is when the BBC’s editorial voice speaks too much as one to the exclusion of others
[normal]… Coordination [of news output] can lead to homogeneity; and that can be intensified by regulati
[normal]on that sees there being ‘right and ‘wrong’ answers”.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]“A properly resourced service independent of the BBC could provide bracing competition and increase choice for audiences. There may be other i
[normal]deas across all media that should be given a go too”.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]“The hard question for the corporation is why in a digital age it should have the whole pie to itself forever – when doing something different m
[normal]ight be better for the public good”.
